<span id="freeTextContainer6465917288625446310">I dnf&apos;d this book because I swapped to <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1490772354' rel='nofollow noopener'>audio</a> (proper review there). I wanted to read this book because of this review which made me laugh:<br/><br/><i>&quot;I have spent the last week or so with words going through my brain that one cannot use in the real world. There was not only the oft-repeated word for a black person that was common in the 18th century, but there was constant use of the c-word and the p-word for female genitalia and the c-word for mail genitalia and the f-word for what the f-word really means</i></span>
  <span id="freeText6465917288625446310" style="display:none">I dnf'd this book because I swapped to <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1490772354" rel="nofollow noopener">audio</a> (proper review there). I wanted to read this book because of this review which made me laugh:<br /><br /><i>"I have spent the last week or so with words going through my brain that one cannot use in the real world. There was not only the oft-repeated word for a black person that was common in the 18th century, but there was constant use of the c-word and the p-word for female genitalia and the c-word for mail genitalia and the f-word for what the f-word really means."</i><br /><br />Why can't she just say cunt, pussy, cock and fuck? It didn't kill the author. What is she so worried about, that she might fall off her moral high pedestal if she utters them?<br /><br />Since she listened to the book she can't use a black marker in the book that another reviewer I read does (I hope they aren't library books). It makes you laugh, doesn't it?<br /><br />So I'm going to read it.</span>
