<div id="review_2883823608" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2883823608" />
    <a title="Dave Marsland" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18712005-dave-marsland"><img alt="Dave Marsland" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591371334p2/18712005.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2883823608?book_show_action=true">Mar 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dave Marsland" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dave Marsland" href="/user/show/18712005-dave-marsland">Dave Marsland</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2883823608" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer764753155917623868">It&apos;s so difficult to review this book. It had been sat on my bookshelf for a decade and I kept making excuses not to read it. The truth is, I was scared of it. Scared of ugly truths. It&apos;s written in patois which takes a wee while to understand. It&apos;s a book about slavery, the fictictious slave master gives all his slaves Greek names because he has a predilection for tragedy. The violence is hideous and unremitting. But it&apos;s a compelling read, full of strong female characters. If you want to under</span>
  <span id="freeText764753155917623868" style="display:none">It's so difficult to review this book. It had been sat on my bookshelf for a decade and I kept making excuses not to read it. The truth is, I was scared of it. Scared of ugly truths. It's written in patois which takes a wee while to understand. It's a book about slavery, the fictictious slave master gives all his slaves Greek names because he has a predilection for tragedy. The violence is hideous and unremitting. But it's a compelling read, full of strong female characters. If you want to understand slavery then I implore you to read The Book of Night Women. Not for the faint hearted, but unforgettable.</span>
  <a data-text-id="764753155917623868" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
